narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I'd only recommend it to someone who really loves reading the type of literature we read. I'd also be hesitant to recommend it to people who like to get by without doing all the work, because then there's not much reason to take the course.
Professor Roffman is passionate, but no less tactful.
Read/pretend you read a lot of really great books, talk about them, think about them, write papers. They are more related and aware of each other than you might think. Do it.
